// Root WIT package for Aureline's Wasm / WIT extension-host capability
// worlds. This package is the reserved top-level namespace every
// Aureline-authored capability world belongs to.
//
// Authoritative: docs/adr/0019-wasm-wit-extension-host-and-capability-worlds.md
// Narrative: docs/extensions/wit_host_contract_seed.md
// Registry: artifacts/extensions/capability_worlds.yaml
// Negotiation schema: schemas/extensions/host_negotiation.schema.json
//
// Versioning rules (ADR-0019):
//   - Package version follows semver. Additive field / record /
//     resource / function additions are minor. Repurposing a named
//     item is major and requires a new decision row.
//   - World slugs under this package are reserved; retired slugs are
//     never reused.
//   - Third-party worlds MUST NOT mint identities under the
//     `aureline:` namespace.
//
// Invariants (ADR-0019, binding):
//   - Every world resolves the ADR-0018 trust-decision packet before
//     a capability fires; a handle issued under `trusted` MUST NOT
//     survive downgrade to `restricted`.
//   - Raw Wasm component bytes, raw module bytes, raw helper-binary
//     invocation bodies, raw bridge-shim payloads, raw signing-key
//     material, and raw policy-bundle bytes never cross the world
//     boundary.
//   - Filesystem-touching worlds bind to the ADR-0006 VFS path
//     identity; extensions never crawl disk directly.
//   - Credential-requesting worlds project through the ADR-0007
//     handle classes; raw secret bytes never cross.
//   - Shell / task / recipe worlds resolve the ADR-0009 execution
//     context before capabilities fire.
//   - Provider-linked worlds quote the ADR-0010 grant-resolution
//     vocabulary.
//   - Every world's capability row carries the ADR-0011 five-axis
//     lifecycle markers.

package aureline:worlds@0.1.0;

/// Default host-negotiated capability surface. An extension manifest
/// (ADR-0012) declares this world when it consumes any subset of the
/// reserved Aureline capability worlds under one negotiation.
///
/// The concrete capability set is projected at negotiation time from
/// `declared_capability_worlds` -> `offered_capability_worlds` ->
/// `negotiated_capability_worlds`. The packet is recorded as
/// `host_negotiation_packet` in
/// `schemas/extensions/host_negotiation.schema.json`.
world aureline-host {
    import editor-read: interface "aureline:editor-read/editor-read@0.1.0";
    import workspace-read: interface "aureline:workspace-read/workspace-read@0.1.0";
    import diff-apply-preview: interface "aureline:diff-apply-preview/diff-apply-preview@0.1.0";
    import terminal-observe: interface "aureline:terminal-observe/terminal-observe@0.1.0";
    import network-egress: interface "aureline:network-egress/network-egress@0.1.0";
}
